utilities

Class MySort

  • java.lang.Object
    • utilities.MySort

  • public class MySort
extends java.lang.Object
    A class that contains six different types of sorts: Bubble, Selection, Insertion, Merge, Quick and Cocktail sort. Each sort has two methods comparing elements using either the compareTo() or compare() method.
    Version:
    1.0 Created on February 20, 2020
    Author:
    Casey Majandog

      • partitionComparable

        private static int partitionComparable(java.util.ArrayList<Shape> list,
                                       int leftIndex,
                                       int rightIndex)
        Takes values of left index and compares them to the pivot point. If the value is greater than the pivot point then the right value and the left value swap places. Compares the values using the compareTo() method.
        Parameters:
        list - An Array list of type Shape.
        leftIndex - Index of values left of the pivot.
        rightIndex - Index of values right of the pivot.
        Returns:
        The next pivot point.
